UML:TaggedValue.value: The MUDDI (Model for Underground Data Definition and Integration) package comprises a profile of abstract entities from the MUDDI conceptual data model as well as standard codelists for selected attributes of those entities and basic relations between network entities.
QualityLevelValue: <<CodeList>> Survey quality levels from ASCE 38-02 (A-D) and PAS128 (QL-A - QL-D)
Marker Type Codelist Codelist of marker types, either survey / observation features or physically visible indicators of asset depth / location

MUDDIObject: <<FeatureType>> The parent class of underground infrastructure or other underground environment features. Its mandatory and optional attributes are inherited by all more specialized classes in the MUDDI core model and derived NUAR Harmonized Model. Mandatory attributes: assetID assetOwner businessContact emergencyContact horizontalCRS systemID systemLoadDate
assetID: {id} mandatory This an identifier assigned uniquely by an asset owner. It should be as stable and persistent as possible relative to that particular physical asset or defined region.
assetOperator: Optional Name / identity of the asset operator if distinct from the asset owner
assetOwner: Mandatory Name / identity of the asset owner. Discrete contact details are stored in <ContactDetails> objects with "assetOwner" = "businessName"
azimuth: Optional Horizontal angle (measured clockwise) of the length dimension of a utility feature with respect to a north base line. The azimuth for circular objects is zero.
businessContact: Mandatory Contact information for the asset responsible party

centroidXYZ: Optional X-Y-Z coordinates representing the center of the utility feature for data exchange purposes. For non-linear structures, XYZ represents an anchor point used for 3D representations, which may or not coincide with the feature’s centroid. In many cases, XYZ coincides with the observed location in the field (e.g., center of manhole lid). For proper orientation in a 3D space, the Azimuth attribute is also necessary. (ASCE_AsBuilt)

certification: Optional Name and credentials of the party (if any) that certified the data as meeting Positional Accuracy requirements as described in Table 1 and attribute data requirements as agreed for data exchange purposes. (ASCE_AsBuilt).

dataSensitivityLevel: Optional Indicator of the sensitivity level of the data recorded for a utility feature. If the data are considered sensitive security information (SSI), the data must be labeled on any output produced and handled appropriately (ASCE As-built).
dateDataCollected: Optional Date when a utility feature was surveyed in the field. (ASCE As-built)

depth: Optional Numerical value in measurementUnits of the depth from grade at time of survey to the top of the asset. This attribute should be used for a single approximation of asset depth according to depthMethod. More detailed / precise vertical positioning information should be represented in a geometry attribute.
depthMethod: Optional The method by which the value for depth was determined. Values for this attribute are defined in the <DepthMethodValue> codelist
emergencyContact: Mandatory Contact information (telephone number, etc.) to reach the responsible party in the event of an emergency involving this asset.

featureType: Optional Category of utility feature based on feature function and configuration. Function refers to the main purpose of the utility feature. Configuration refers to geometric and structural characteristics of the utility feature. Depending on the implementation, feature differentiation may be at the feature class level (e.g., separate feature classes for devices, access points, support structures, and so on) or by attribute. Because of the small number of potential feature types, feature differentiation at the feature class level is common. Values for featureType are defined in the <FeatureTypeValue> codelist

horizontalAccuracy: Optional Circular error of a dataset’s horizontal coordinates at the 95% confidence level, where 95% of positional accuracies are equal to or smaller than the reported accuracy value. It takes into account the combined effect of all X and Y errors. (ASCE As-built)
horizontalCRS: Mandatory Coordinate system, datum, and epoch date (if applicable) associated with the X and Y coordinates. (ASCE As-built)

intendedPermanence: Optional Intended longevity of the utility feature. Depending on the implementation, most databases would probably only handle permanent features under the assumption that temporary features occupy the right-of- way for a limited period, after which the permit requires the removal of those features. However, if the temporary accommodation is via a lease (e.g., a temporary water line to support oil or gas shale developments), tracking the status of the temporary feature at any time may be important. (ASCE As-built) Values for intendedPermanence are defined in the <IntendedPermanenceValue> codelist

material: Optional Predominant or conveying material of which the utility feature is constructed. For features that transmit a signal or electrical power, material refers to the conductor material. (ASCE). This is presently a CharacterString but values can be drawn from the <MaterialTypeValue> codelist

measurementUnits: Optional Units used to express height, width, length, and wall thickness. For data exchange purposes, the units of measurement are the same for all dimensions. (ASCE). Values for measurementUnits are defined in the <MeasurementUnitsValue> codelist
operationalStatus: Optional Operational status of the utility feature. Values for operationalStatus are defined in the <OperationalStatusValue> codelist
qualityLevel: Optional Quality level in accordance with ASCE/CI 38- 02 / PAS128. Values for qualityLevel are defined in the <QualityLevelValue> codelist
systemID: Mandatory Identifier for this data record defined by and globally unique within the system that stores the data record
systemLoadDate: Mandatory Date at which the data record for this entity was last loaded into the datastore system.
undergroundStatus: Optional Indicator of whether the feature is partially or completely underground. (ASCE) The values for undergroundStatus are defined in the <UndergroundStatusValue> codelist.
version: Optional The version specifier for the present data record.

verticalAccuracy: Optional Linear error of a dataset’s vertical coordinates at the 95% confidence level, where 95% of positional accuracies are equal to or smaller than the reported accuracy value. It takes into account the effect of all Z errors. Positional Accuracy is different from the root-mean-squared (RMS) error.(ASCE)
verticalCRS: Optional Datum, etc. for the Z coordinate. (ASCE) This is the absolute Z coordinate, not the depth from grade
Conveyance Category Codelist Codelist of roles that particular network segments play in overall network conveyance, e.g. Trunk vs Distribution.
Container Type Codelist Codelist of container types
Network: <<FeatureType>> MUDDIObject that represents a whole or partial infrastructure network
utilitySubType: Optional Type of utility service at a finer level of disaggregation than utility type. The values for utilitySubType are defined in the <UtilitySubTypeValue> codelist.
utilityType: Optional Type of utility service that a utility feature carries (ASCE). The values for utilityType are defined in the <UtilityTypeValue> codelist.
Network aggregates a set of links
Network aggregates a set of nodes
NetworkFacility: <<FeatureType>> Network-specific facility containing network assets, typically secured and/or associated with restricted access / information policies (ASCE "Secured Utility Area")
bufferSize: Optional Width of additional restricted or secure buffer zone around a NetworkFacility in measurementUnits
facilityType: Optional Type of facility. Values for facilityType are defined in the <FacilityTypeValue> codelist
utilitySubType: Optional Type of utility service at a finer level of disaggregation than utility type. The values for utilitySubType are defined in the <UtilitySubTypeValue> codelist.
utilityType: Optional Type of utility service that a utility feature carries (ASCE). The values for utilityType are defined in the <UtilityTypeValue> codelist.
Utility Subtype Codelist Codelist of utility subtypes that classify utilities at a secondary level, such as surface water vs combined sewer.
Support Type Codelist Codelist of types of utility asset supports, e.g. Footing vs Tower.
SupportObject: <<FeatureType>> Structure serving primarily as a support, platform, or foundation for another infrastructure component. (ASCE "Supporting Structure").
supportType: Optional Type of Support. The values for supportType are defined in the <SupportTypeValue> codelist

Surface Component Type Codelist Codelist of specific types of Network Surface Nodes, pertaining specifically to their aspects visible at or above grade. These may be redundant with derived network feature types and supplemented by more specific component type codelists. It allows new surface utility feature types to be added without changing the model.
Marker: <<FeatureType>> Specific location for an Infrastructure observation such as depth or cross section which may or may not be physically marked
linkedFile: Optional Link to a file associated to the marker, e.g. a cross-section diagram.
markerType: Optional Type of Marker. The values for markerType are defined in the <MarkerTypeValue> codelist

Component Type Codelist Codelist of specific types of NetworkObjects. These may be redundant with derived network feature types and supplemented by more specific component type codelists. It allows new utility feature types to be added without changing the model.
Operational Status Codelist Codelist of operational status values for MUDDIObjects

Underground Status Codelist Codelist of underground status, e.g. Underground vs. Surface, Utility assets which are not fully buried may still be represented in this model so as to provide important information and constraints on underground utility infrastructure.
Conveyance Method Codelist Codelist of methods by which utility commodities are conveyed through a network asset, e.g. gravity vs pumped.
Facility Type Codelist Codelist of types of utility facilities including those (Redacted Site) for which no specific facility information is being made available.

NetworkNode: <<FeatureType>> Discrete utility feature that is directly involved with the conveyance, control, or distribution of a particular utility service and serves as a node in a network graph. (ASCE "Device")
Material Type Codelist Codelist of utility asset constituent materials.
NetworkObject: <<FeatureType>> Asset that has a role in a utility network.

component: Optional Utility feature subtype. A component is an element of a utility system, which corresponds to the lowest level of utility feature disaggregation for data exchange purposes. Depending on the implementation, component differentiation may be at the feature class level or by attribute. Because of the substantial number of different components in a utility system, differentiation by attribute is more common than at the feature class level. The component domain may be expanded as needed. (ASCE As-built). Values for component are defined in the <ComponentValue> codelist

conveyanceCategory: Optional Primary category or purpose of service of the utility feature. Included in each category is the supporting infrastructure, such as alarm and ventilation, needed to provide the corresponding utility service. Values for conveyanceCategory are defined in the <ConveyanceCategoryValue> codelist.

conveyanceMethod: Optional Method to move or convey matter (the utility commodity) through the utility feature. (ASCE). Values for conveyanceMethod are defined in the <ConveyanceMethodValue> codelist, including both pressure and voltage ranges.

fillMaterial: Optional Material used to fill the space between a utility feature and its encasement or an out-of- service feature. (ASCE "interstitialMaterial"). This is presently a CharacterString but values can be drawn from the <MaterialTypeValue> codelist

insideHeight: Optional For circular shaped segments, not applicable. For non-circular shaped segments, maximum inside height of cross-sectional shape. For features other than segments, maximum inside height of feature.(ASCE). Units are always defined by <<measurementUnits>>

insideLength: Optional For segments, not applicable. For features other than segments, maximum inside length of feature (measured in the horizontal plane, perpendicular to the width). Units are always defined by <<measurementUnits>>

insideWidth: Optional For circular shaped segments, inside diameter of the utility feature cross section. For non-circular shaped segments, maximum inside width of cross-sectional shape. For features other than segments, maximum inside width of feature. Units are always defined by <<measurementUnits>>
isCathodicProtected: Optional Indicator of the presence of a cathodic protection.(ASCE)
isEncased: Optional Indicator of the presence of encasement to insulate or protect the utility feature.(ASCE)
isFilled: Optional Indicator of the presence of interstitial material inside the infrastructure encasement.(ASCE)

isNPS: Optional Indicator that the provided outside Width is a "Nominal Pipe Size" rather than a true measure. This may correspond to knwn inside and outside dimensions for well-known types of pipes or other network elements. If isNPS is true and both outside and inside width are set to the same value, then it is not known what dimension the value applies to.

outerMaterial: Optional Material from which the outer covering, carrier pipe, insulation, etc. is constructed, This is presently a CharacterString but values can be drawn from the <MaterialTypeValue> codelist

outsideWidth: Optional For circular shaped segments, outside diameter of the utility feature cross section. For non-circular shaped segments, maximum outside width of cross-sectional shape. For features other than segments, maximum outside width of feature. Units are always defined by <<measurementUnits>>

protectiveMaterial: Optional Material from which protective layers or elements of the object are constructed. This is presently a CharacterString but values can be drawn from the <MaterialTypeValue> codelist
utilitySubType: Optional Type of utility service at a finer level of classification than utility type. The values for utilitySubType are defined in the <UtilitySubTypeValue> codelist.
utilityType: Optional Type of utility service that a utility feature carries (ASCE). The values for utilityType are defined in the <UtilityTypeValue> codelist.
wallThickness: Optional Maximum wall thickness.(ASCE) Units are always defined by <<measurementUnits>>
NetworkLink: <<FeatureType>> Linear utility feature that serves as a link or edge in a network graph. (ASCE "Segment")

downstreamDepth: Optional Numerical value in measurementUnits of the depth from grade at time of survey or other determination method to the top of the downstream end of the asset. IF this attribute is provided for a NetworkLink feature, then the depth attribute should be understood as upstreamDepth. This attribute should be used for a single approximation of asset depth according to depthMethod. More detailed / precise vertical positioning information should be represented in a geometry attribute.
Planning Region Codelist Codelist of planning region types. Redundant with derived planning region feature types but allows new region types to be defined without changing the model.

Utility Type Codelist Codelist of utility types for MUDDIObjects. Redundant with utility-specific derived feature types, but allows generic or hybrid asset information to be represented, or new utility types to be added without changing the model.
Intended Permanence Codelist Codelist of values for intended permanence

Feature Type Codelist: Codelist of feature types for MUDDIObjects. This may be redundant with the name of a derived feature, but allows generic utility information to be typed and also allows new feature types to be added without changing the model.
Depth Method Codelist Codelist of methods by which the stated depth of a utility asset has been detemined.
Measurement Units Codelist Codelist of attribute value measurement units
PlanningRegion: <<FeatureType>> Defined region with characteristics relevant to excavation planning.
planningRegionType: Optional Type of Planning Region. The values for PlanningRegion are defined in the <PlanningRegionValue> codelist.
policyName: Optional The policy with which this PlanningRegion is associated, such as permission to dig or notification of activity.
ContainerObject: <<FeatureType>> Underground or surface structure that serves primarily as a container for other structures, such as a vault, arcade, or conduit. (ASCE "Containing Structure")
containerType: Optional Type of Containe. The values for containerType are defined in the <ContainerTypeValue> codelist
NetworkSurfaceNode: <<FeatureType>> A Network Node that has a visible surface aspect. (ASCE "Access Point")
surfaceComponent: Optional Component subtype specific to NetworkSurfaceNode. Values for surfaceComponent are defined in the <SurfaceComponentValue> codelist
